quick question about windows vista just wondering if i install windows vista on my computer will i still keep all of my programs data music etc or will it delete everything thanks that depends on the install if you are doing a clean install then no everything will go away if you doing an upgrade then everything will be kept first make sure your computer has the minimum requirements for vista detailed on the end of the box also be advised that a lot of the soundcards video cards ect and programs are not supported by vista so be very careful Compact audio cassette ZX Spectrum Apple II family Amstrad CPC Floppy disk TRS-80 Atari 8-bit family Commodore VIC-20 Commodore DOS Amiga Disk operating system Commodore Plus/4 Commodore PET Commodore International Read-only memory MOS Technology SID History of operating systems Forth programming language Copy protection Original Amiga chipset Cartridge (electronics) Video game music DOS Commodore BASIC Commodore 128 Locomotive BASIC Action Replay Warez BASIC programming language AmigaOS Home computer Type-in program PlayStation Portable History of computing hardware (1960s-present) Enterprise content management Datassette Coleco Adam Atari ST MiniDisc System 7 (Macintosh) Windows XP Cache Acorn Electron Windows 3.x Macintosh Finder Intellivision America Online Commodore 1541 Texas Instruments TI-99/4A IBM PC compatible Sega Mega Drive/Sega Genesis Xbox Synthesizer Atari 2600 CP/M SAM Coup__ Video game crash of 1983 MS-DOS Linux Computer storage Hard disk Web server Apple IIGS Disk cloning ITunes VHS Gramophone record KIM-1 Redundant array of independent disks TiVo Ultima III DVD Embedded system Non-Maskable interrupt BBC Master Famicom Disk System Patch (computing) IBM 1130 Sinclair ZX81 Secure Digital card History of computer and video games IBM PC PlayStation 3 Memory (computers) Screenshot Sound recording Magnetic tape Common Unix Printing System IBM PCjr Electronic music CPU design Wget Disk image Graphics BASIC WordStar Comm